[heading Header]
`#include <boost/afio/afio.hpp>`

[heading Complexity]Amortised O(N) to dispatch. Amortised O(N/threadpool) to complete.
[heading Exception Model]Propagates exceptions of any input preconditions with an errored state at the point of dispatch, and throws a `std::runtime_error` if any inputs have values which could not possibly be correct. Once a batch of input ops has been verified at the point of entry as not errored, you are guaranteed that the batch is atomically scheduled as a whole, unless one of the following conditions occurs: (i) A failure to allocate memory occurs.
